This paper deals with the security and privacy of cryptographic keys, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The use of a central server suggests that it may also fall under the categories of distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses privacy-preserving protocols, which could fall under the categories of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
